Source-Makefile: feeds/ibase/opkg/Makefile
Package: opkg
Version: 9c97d5ecd795709c8584e972bfdf3aee3a5b846d-6
Depends:  
Menu-Depends: 
Provides: 
Build-Variant: unsigned
Build-Types: host
Section: base
Category: Base system
Title: opkg package manager
Maintainer: Jo-Philipp Wich <xm@subsignal.org>
Source: opkg-9c97d5ecd795709c8584e972bfdf3aee3a5b846d.tar.gz
Type: ipkg
Description:     Lightweight package management system
  opkg is the opkg Package Management System, for handling
  installation and removal of packages on a system. It can
  recursively follow dependencies and download all packages
  necessary to install a particular package.

  opkg knows how to install both .ipk and .deb packages.
http://wiki.openmoko.org/wiki/Opkg
Jo-Philipp Wich <xm@subsignal.org>
@@

Package: opkg-smime
Version: 9c97d5ecd795709c8584e972bfdf3aee3a5b846d-6
Depends:  +libopenssl
Menu-Depends: 
Provides: 
Build-Variant: smime
Build-Types: host
Section: base
Category: Base system
Title: opkg package manager (with S/MIME signature support)
Maintainer: Jo-Philipp Wich <xm@subsignal.org>
Source: opkg-9c97d5ecd795709c8584e972bfdf3aee3a5b846d.tar.gz
Type: ipkg
Description:     Lightweight package management system
  opkg is the opkg Package Management System, for handling
  installation and removal of packages on a system. It can
  recursively follow dependencies and download all packages
  necessary to install a particular package.

  opkg knows how to install both .ipk and .deb packages.

  This package allows the Package index to be verified with S/MIME.
http://wiki.openmoko.org/wiki/Opkg
Jo-Philipp Wich <xm@subsignal.org>
@@


